## Hypothesis
Implied volatility reflects market expectations of future uncertainty, while Parkinson volatility captures historical realized volatility using high-low price ranges.

When implied volatility (calls) is significantly higher than historical volatility, it suggests that the market expects higher future movement, often associated with bullish sentiment or upcoming events.

Thus, a higher ratio of implied volatility to historical volatility indicates potential upside opportunities.

Using ts_backfill ensures missing data is handled and avoids signal sparsity.

